Paper: hep-th/9805217

Date: 1998-05-29

Title: Near Horizon Superspace

Authors: R. Kallosh, J. Rahmfeld, and A. Rajaraman

Comments: 11 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: JHEP 9809 (1998) 002

The adS_{p+2} x S^{d-p-2} geometry of the near horizon branes is promoted toconnection and form superfields are found. This supergeometry can be used forthe construction of new superconformal theories. We also discuss theGreen-Schwarz action for a type IIB string on adS_5 x S_5.